      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HORRIBLE HANK (2) closed off strongly last start to get up for second, beaten one length, over 1200m at Dalby. Record at this journey is impressive with three wins and three placings from nine runs and is a definite leading contender. VICTORY'S GHOST (7) was in the firing line on the bend and progressed nicely last start to finish a close third over 1400m at Rockhampton after missing the placings at the previous appearance. Tackling a more suitable race so he is all set to build on that latest effort. NICCONORI (6) scored first-up two runs ago but couldn't back it up last time when sixth over 1200m at Rockhampton. Can turn things around. KEYBOARD (5) was in the money two starts back at Emerald but couldn't repeat it last time when sixth, beaten 7 lengths, at Rockhampton over 1050m. Has her share of talent and can do a lot better.",
